    • Constructor Detail

      • Equipment

        public Equipment​(int type,
                 int lv)
        Class Equipment Constructor -> for random generated Equipment; see: loadRarity() / loadStats()

        Call to super initializes a "" name and a quantity of 1.

        Additionally initializes the loc in String[][][] equipments, name based on its location, a random rarity, stars based on the rarity, and stats based on the loc in int[][][][] equipmentStats.

        Parameters:
        type - 0 for body armor ; 1 for accessories
        lv - Character's level

      • Equipment

        public Equipment​(String name,
                 int rar)
        Class Equipment Constructor -> when specifying which Equipment to construct; see: loadRarity() / loadStats()

        Call to super initializes name based on param name

        Search through the String[][][] equipments based on param name -> initializes loc based on its location -> rarity based on param rar, stars based on the rarity, and stats based on the loc in int[][][][] equipmentStats.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the Equipment (Item)
        rar - the rarity/stars to give to Equipment

      • Equipment

        public Equipment​(Item toConvert)
        Class Equipment Constructor -> for converting an Item to an Equipment; used: Player.openInterface()

        call to super initializes name of Equipment

        Additionally initializes stars, rarity, stats, and loc based on param toConvert's instances

        Parameters:
        toConvert - Item to convert to Equipment

    • Method Detail

      • loadStats

        public void loadStats()
        Initializes int[] stats based on loc

        Additional stats is added based on rarity (stars): loc[1] (y value of String[][][] equipments) * stars + (stars - 1)

      • loadRarity

        public void loadRarity​(int rar)
        Initializes String rarity based on param rar

        1) If param rar == -1, randomize rarity: Unique(7): 1% | Archaic(6): 2% | Legendary(5): 3% | Epic(4): 5% | Rare(3): 10% | Uncommon(2): 19% | Common(1): 60%

        2) if param rar given: initializes rarity accordingly

        Parameters:
        rar - the rarity of Equipment; -1 to randomize rarity

      • getCost

        public int getCost​(int lv)
        Get the cost of an Equipment based on Character's level.

        Cost of Equipment is Character's level * 50 * rarity (stars)

        Parameters:
        lv - Character's level
        Returns:
        the cost of an Equipment
